<HEADLINE> DPRK Refutes U.S. Rumor of "Threat From North Korea" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The United States regards the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) as an imaginary enemy
with ulterior motives so as to achieve military Hegemonism, a
commentary of the Korean Central News Agency said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Strobe Talbott, deputy secretary of the U.S. State Department,
officially made a provocative statement at a press conference on
June 4 that the DPRK is the imaginary enemy of the U.S. "national
missile defense" initiative, according to the commentary.
</P>
<P>
"The U.S. authorities are spreading such rumor of 'missile
threat from north Korea' to achieve two aims. One is to retain
monopoly of missiles and realize its military domination over the
world by establishing the 'national missile defense' system at any
cost under the pretext of the 'missile threat' from the DPRK. The
other is to isolate and suffocate the DPRK politically and
militarily by branding it as a 'missile proliferating state'," it
said.
</P>
<P>
"This brings into bolder relief the long-standing U.S.
dominationist ambition and impudence. It also eloquently shows
that the U.S. call for 'dialogue and cooperation,' 'peace and
disarmament' is nothing but sheer hypocrisy," it added. "The DPRK
and the United States are in the process of dialogue. Action
getting on dialogue partner's nerves should be avoided to advance
dialogue and establish cooperative relations."
</P>
<P>
The commentary warned that "this impudence of the U.S. may
throw a grave obstacle in the way of improving relations with the
DPRK."
</P>
<P>
"Unless the U.S. discards its intention to stifle the DPRK, the
latter will have no option but to take a strong countermeasure,"
it said.
</P>
<P>
"In that case the situation will not be in favor of the United
States and it will be held wholly responsible for all the
consequences arising therefrom," the commentary ended. 
</P>
</TEXT>
