<HEADLINE> European Championship Finals History </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Finalists and scores from previous
European soccer championship finals:
</P>
<P>
1960: Soviet Union beat Yugoslavlia 2-1
</P>
<P>
1964: Spain bt Soviet Union 2-1
</P>
<P>
1968: Italy bt Yugoslavia 2-0
</P>
<P>
1972: West Germany bt Soviet Union 3-0
</P>
<P>
1976: Czechoslovakia ties with West Germany 2-2 (Czechoslovakia
wins 5-3 on penalty kicks)
</P>
<P>
1980: West Germany bt Belgium 2-1
</P>
<P>
1984: France bt Spain 2-0
</P>
<P>
1988: Netherlands bt Soviet Union 2-0
</P>
<P>
1992: Denmark bt Germany 2-0
</P>
<P>
1996: Germany bt Czech Republic 2-1
</P>
</TEXT>
