<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Pays Tribute to National Patriots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
said Friday that the patriots who laid down their lives for the
freedom will have died in vain if the freedom they died for is not
translated into social, economic and political development.
</P>
<P>
Museveni made the remarks when officiating at the national
function to mark the 11th Heroes Day celebrations in Nakasongola
district, according to a press release from the President's Office
Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The president paid high tribute to the patriots of Uganda who
liberated the country from tyranny and to those who are still
sacrificing so that all Ugandans can live in peace and security,
the release said.
</P>
<P>
The heroes being celebrated were driven by the ideals of
freedom, democracy, peace and security, Museveni was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The celebrations were attended by thousands of people from all
over the country and especially from Luwero Triangle, the cradle
of the liberation struggle of the National Resistance Movement in
the early 1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
