<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECO Leaders Call for Establishment of ECO Bank, Reinsurance Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Member countries of the Economic
Cooperation Organization (ECO) ended a one-day summit here on
Saturday with a call for the early establishment of a collective
trade and development bank and a reinsurance company, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The 10 members should complete the pending formalities as soon
as possible for the early establishment of the bank and the
reinsurance company, leaders of the member states said in a
statement known as the "Tehran Declaration".
</P>
<P>
The sixth summit of the regional economic group was attended by
heads of state of seven member states, namely Iranian President
Mohammad Khatami, Pakistan's Chief Executive Pervez Musharaf,
Presidents Askar Akayev of Kyrgyzstan, Saparmurad Niyazov of
Turkmenistan, Geidar Aliyev of Azerbaijan, Islam Karimov of
Uzbekistan and Emomali Rakhmonov of Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Presidents of Kazakhstan and Turkey are represented respectively
by the Kazakh prime minister and Turkish minister of state for
economic affairs. Afghan President Burhanuddin Rabbani, who was
ousted by the current ruling Taliban militia in 1996 but enjoys
Iranian support, was also present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, leaders of the member states also called for
closer cooperation in economic, technical, scientific, educational
and cultural fields, as well as infrastructure in the region.
</P>
<P>
The summit reiterated the need to provide landlocked oil and gas
producing ECO members with access to the world energy markets,
expressing satisfaction with the regional arrangements made by the
member states for transporting the region's oil and gas to
different parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
It also welcomed the appointment of Iran's Abdolrahim Gavahi as
the new secretary-general of ECO with effect from August 13, 2000,
and expressed confidence that he would continue the present course
on promoting regional cooperation. Gavahi is also advisor to
Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi.
</P>
<P>
The summit stressed the importance of international cooperation,
which is critical in addressing challenges of globalization. It
called for the full participation of developing countries in the
international economic and financial policies decision-making
process.
</P>
<P>
It also underlined the principle of universal membership of the
World Trade Organization (WTO) and called for acceleration of the
accession process without political considerations.
</P>
<P>
All the members of the WTO should refrain from placing excessive
demands on developing countries seeking accession to the
international body, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Tehran-based ECO was founded by Iran, Pakistan and Turkey in
1985 and joined later by the Central Asian and Caucasian republics
after the collapse of the former Soviet Union in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
