<HEADLINE> Panama To Seek Canadian Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Panamanian mission, made up of government officials and
private sector leaders, led by the Private Enterprise National
Council (CONEP), and the Panamanian Exporters Association, also
seeks to increase trade exchanges in the tourism and maritime
areas.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian delegation will hold, during its visit to Ottawa,
the Canadian capital, a meeting with Canadian Vice Premier Herb
Gray and with Canadian businessmen, and will attend a session of
the Parliament of Canada, the country that will preside over the
Third Summit of the Americas in the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will tour the cities of Montreal, Quebec, and
Toronto, where they will hold trade meetings with businessmen of
that country.
</P>
<P>
Panama imported from Canada some 30 million U.S. dollars worth
of commodities in 1999 and exported six million dollars to that
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
