Saunders, was shot dead by two members of the November 17, a
terrorist group in Greece, and the Greek police investigation
aimed at tracking down and arrest the attackers continued Saturday
with the participation of Scotland Yard officers as well as the
FBI team in Athens and other U.S. specialists who arrived here
after the killing of Saunders.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the Athens prosecutor with a urgent
request to the U.S. court authorities asked that former CIA chief
James Wesley testify in Greece regarding his interview with a
Greek newspaper that the November 17 terrorists were acquainted
with Greek government ministers.
</P>
<P>
Greece has insisted that there are no lists with names of
terrorist suspects. 
