<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Syrian President Hafez al-Assad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The following is a chronology of
Syrian President Hafez al-Assad, who died of heart attack Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hafez al-Assad, president of Syria, was born in a farmer's
family at Latakia province on October 6, 1930. He was educated in
Syrian military colleges.
</P>
<P>
Assad joined the Baath party in 1946, and then formed the
Baathist Military Committee when he was in Egypt. He was promoted
to be General of the Air Force in 1964. He served as Minister of
Defense and Commander of the Air Force from 1966 to 1970. Then he
served as Syrian Prime Minister from 1970 to 1971, and Secretary of
the Baath party in November 1970.
</P>
<P>
Assad was the secretary of the regional leadership of the Baath
party in May 1971 and General Secretary of the party's national
leadership. Assad was also a member of the Presidential Council of
the Federation of the Arab Republics, which consists of Syria,
Egypt and Libya in 1971. He has been the president of the Syrian
National Progressive Front since 1972, and Commander-in-Chief of
the Armed Forces since 1973.
</P>
<P>
Assad was elected president of Syria in March 1971 and re-
elected in 1978, 1985, 1992 and 1999 to serve a seven-year term. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
