<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT Syrian Parliament Announces Assad's Death, Ready to Amend Constitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad
died Saturday morning, Syrian parliament announced in its
extraordinary session Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The lawmakers stood in silence in tribute to the late president,
who had been in power since 1971, according to Syrian state
television which broadcast live.
</P>
<P>
The parliament has decided to set up a special committee to
amend the constitution and lower the age threshold for the
presidency. The current constitution requires any Syrian who wants
to run for the president should be above 40.
</P>
<P>
This is believed to pave the way for Assad's favorite son,
Bashar, 35, to assume power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
