<HEADLINE> Eighteen Killed in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people, including 13
militants and three security personnel, were killed in Jammu and
Kashmir since Friday night, the Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Three security personnel and two militants were killed in an
encounter in Surankote sector of Poonch district in west Kashmir
on Saturday morning, the PTI quoted an official spokesman in
Srinagar, capital of Jammu and Kashmir, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Four militants were killed in another exchange of fire during a
search operation by security forces in Kupwara district, the
spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Security personnel also arrested a top figure of a militant
outfit identified as Tariq Ahmed Antoo in Jammu and Kashmir on
Friday night, he told the PTI. 
</P>
</TEXT>
