<P>
KAMPALA -- Fighting between Ugandan and Rwandan forces on
Friday killed 100 and wounded 700 civilians in Kisangani, a
northeast city of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), the
New Vision Daily report Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Bodies littered in the streets of the city with people unable
to collect them for burial as both armies pounded each other with
heavy artillery and small arms. (Uganda-Rwanda-Fighting)
</P>
