</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- A military court in the Turkish Cypriot area has
sentenced 21-year-old Greek Cypriot soldier Giorgos Kasianides to
20 days in jail for "illegal entry" into a military area in
northern Cyprus, local media reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Turkish soldiers seized Kasianides early on Sunday when they
found him in the Turkish Cypriot side of the divided Cypriot
capital Nicosia. Kasianides was in uniform, but carrying no
weapons. (Cyprus-Soldier-Sentence)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- At least 50 people were injured in the collision of
two tourist trains Saturday in Garmisch-Pattenkirchen, a small
mountain city in the southern state of Bavaria, Germany, police
said.
</P>
<P>
The two rack-railway tourist trains collided on the Germany's
highest mountain, the Zugspitze, near the resort town of Garmisch-
Pattenkirchen. (Germany-Train Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- At least 46 people were killed in house collapses,
landslides and flash floods triggered by heavy rains in Uttar
Pradesh state in north India, the Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Three towns, namely Garhwal, Chamoli and Uttarkashi, were cut
off from the rest of the state following snapping of all
communication links, the PTI quoted local officials as saying. (
India-House-Accident) 
</P>
