<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Delegation Visits Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Czech parliament
leaders agreed here Saturday to further expand exchanges and
promote understanding between the parliaments of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with Buhe, vice chairman of the Standing Committee
of China's National People's Congress (NPC), Vice-chairman of the
Chamber of Deputies (lower house) of the Czech Republic Frantisek
Brozik said Buhe's visit helps to promote the mutual understating
between the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Buhe said there are no conflicts of interest between the two
countries, and China is willing to go on developing cooperation
with the Czech Republic in such fields as economy, culture and
education on the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese NPC delegation arrived here Friday on a five-day
visit to the Czech Republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
