<HEADLINE> Burns Wins 1st Stage in Acropolis Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Richard Burns won the
opening special stage of the Acropolis Rally on the second day of
competition Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Driving a Subaru Impreza WRC 2000, Burns finished the first of
Saturday's seven stages, seven seconds ahead of Spaniard Carlos
Sainz's Ford Focus WRC.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Colin McRae finished the stage in fifth place.
</P>
<P>
McRae led the standing Friday, with a 38.5 second advantage
after the first day of the rally. The event ends Sunday and
covers 1,408 kilometers through central Greece.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Didier Auriol was the latest casualty in the grueling
Acropolis Rally, after his Seat Cordoba suffered mechanical
failure. Forty-three drivers have quit the race out of a starting
list of 117. 
</P>
</TEXT>
