<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Chemical Plant Explosion in Eastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and 25
others injured Saturday evening as an explosion ripped through a
chemical plant in Ojima, Gunma Prefecture in eastern Japan.
</P>
<P>
The blast, which occurred at 6 p.m. local time (0900 GMT),
gutted the plant owned by Tokyo-based Nisshin Chemical Co., police
said. Three people were still missing.
</P>
<P>
The explosion caused power failures in more than 200 households
and broke the windows of nearby shops and cars, according to
police.
</P>
<P>
The plant was still on fire two and half hours later when local
residents were evacuating.
</P>
<P>
Nisshin Chemical was a 47-year-old company producing chemicals
such as hydroxylamin and hydrochloride. 
</P>
</TEXT>
