<DOCNO> XIE20000610.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Algerian President to Visit France Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Algerian President Abdelaziz
Bouteflika will visit France on June 13-16, the first by an
Algerian head of state since 1983.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Bouteflika will be given the highest protocol,
including an exceptional welcome ceremony to be presided by French
President Jacques Chirac at the airport upon his arrival.
</P>
<P>
Bouteflika is expected to meet with Chirac and Prime Minister
Lionel Jospin as well as some French business leaders and
representatives of the strong Algerian community in France.
</P>
<P>
Relations between France and Algeria have fully normalized
since Bouteflika came to power in April 1999, after one decade of
cold and sometimes tense relations.
</P>
<P>
But French officials and media have described the relations
between the two countries as "always passionate" because of
cultural and historical ties and the huge Algerian community in
France, including more than 1 million French citizens of Algerian
origin and half a million Algerian nationals.
</P>
<P>
One of the objectives of Bouteflika's visit is to encourage
French enterprises to invest in Algeria, which is experiencing
some social and economic difficulties after a decade of internal
conflict between government forces and Islamic militants, in which
100,000 people were killed.
</P>
<P>
Bouteflika has called on French nationals who used to live in
Algeria before its independence in 1962, to return and join the
country's reconstruction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
