<HEADLINE> China-ROK Forum Held in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh China-ROK Forum on
Future Development opened today in Chongqing, the largest
metropolis in western China.
</P>
<P>
Attending the forum were former president Roh Tae Woo of the
Republic of Korea (ROK), president of the Chinese People's
Institute of Foreign Affairs Mei Zhaorong, and Bao Xuding, mayor
of Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
Roh Taw Woo delivered a keynote speech on development in
northeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The forum originated in 1994 and has been held annually since
then. It was jointly organized by the Chinese People's Institute
of Foreign Affairs and the Korean Foundation of the Republic of
Korea.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day current forum, the two sides will discuss
development in northeast Asia and bilateral economic and trade
cooperation as it relates to China's strategy of developing its
western region.
</P>
<P>
At previous events, officials and experts of the two countries
exchanged views on the international situation and bilateral
cooperation in economic and cultural fields. 
</P>
