<HEADLINE> Recovered Cancer Patients Discuss Caner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-one recovered cancer
patients were invited today to a tumor hospital in east China's
Jiangxi Province to discuss their experiences in battling the
disease.
</P>
<P>
The guests were in high spirits at the meeting, and were called
"stars" by doctors for their remarkable recovery after therapy.
</P>
<P>
All all 31 people, who were suffering from cancer of the lung,
breast, ovary and thyroid gland, are now living normal lives and
have returned to work. The eldest, aged 62, had the disease for 15
years.
</P>
<P>
They said that an optimistic attitude was the key to their
recovery, and that patients must overcome their fear and
disappointment during the course of treatment. 
