<HEADLINE> Kunming Export Fair Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Kunming Export Commodity Trade
Fair closed here today, scoring transactions of 1.9 billion U.S.
dollars, up 7.5 percent over the previous event.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day fair, contracts for 70 projects were
concluded, involving total contractual value of 1.3 billion U.S.
dollars, 12 percent up from the last fair. The projects involve
infrastructure, mining, tourism, environmental protection and
other fields.
</P>
<P>
A British company signed a 500 million US-dollar contract with
Yunnan Metallurgical Group on developing lead-zinc deposits in the
northwestern part of Yunnan province.
</P>
<P>
The fair also secured 35 labor and other projects involving 82
million U.S. dollars and signed 209 contracts among various
regions in China, 50 more than that at the last session.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 foreign businesspeople from 50 countries and
regions and 100,000 Chinese traders attended the fair.  
