<HEADLINE> Indonesian Govt Thanks Foreign Countries For Aid to Bengkulu Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government Saturday
expressed gratitude to a number of countries for the relief aid
they have extended for the benefit of victims of the recent
earthquake in Bengkulu province.
</P>
<P>
The message of thanks was conveyed to the countries concerned
by Defense Minister Juwono Sudarsono as most of the aid had been
channeled through their defense ministries.
</P>
<P>
According to Defense Ministry press statement issued here, a
total of 10 foreign countries had provided aid in the form of
personnel, medical supplies or equipment for the Bengkulu
earthquake victims.
</P>
<P>
The countries were Malaysia, Singapore, Australia, Thailand,
Japan, China, Turkey, the Netherlands, Britain and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
At least 133 persons died in the earthquake that rocked
Bengkulu on Sunday night. The four-minute earthquake knocked out
the province's electricity system and damaged public facilities,
including the governor's office, the local legislative assembly
building and military offices. The strong quake also damaged roads
and toppled electricity poles. 
