<HEADLINE> 46 Die in Torrential Rains in North India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- At least 46 people were killed
in house collapses, landslides and flash floods triggered by heavy
rains in Uttar Pradesh state in north India, the Press Trust of
India (PTI) reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Three towns, namely Garhwal, Chamoli and Uttarkashi, were cut
off from the rest of the state following snapping of all
communication links, the PTI quoted local officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
In Bijnore district in the northern part of Uttar Pradesh, 14
people, mostly women and children, were killed in house collapses
following heavy downpours in the past few days, said the officials.
</P>
<P>
A number of cattle were also killed and property damages in the
district were estimated at tens of millions of rupees, they added.
</P>
<P>
Landslides killed 10 people in Garhwal district, where seven
laborers were swept away in a flooded local river, they said.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains in the past five days also damaged roads in the
state, while continued rainfall was hampering relief and rescue
operations in some districts, said the PTI.
</P>
<P>
As monsoon arrived on time, most parts of north India, which
suffered from a severe drought earlier this year, received heavy
rainfalls in the past week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
