said that the latest military engagement in the area of Guluj and
Tesseny, which began Saturday morning, is continuing. Ethiopian
troops are causing " severe damage to enemy troops" in the intense
fighting, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Eritrea accepted late Friday ceasefire
proposes to end its two-year-old war with Ethiopia, drawn up by
the Organization of African Unity after peace talks in the
Algerian capital Algiers.
