<HEADLINE> UNDP Official on China's Development of Western Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- International organizations
should participate in the development of China's vast western
regions and play a positive role in the expansion, a United
Nations Development Program (UNDP) official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Kerstin Leitner, UNDP resident representative to China, made
the remark today at an international symposium on development of
China's western area, which opened on Thursday in Chongqing,
southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The symposium has been listed as part of UNDP's aid to China
early this year, Leitner said, adding that the project will help
UNDP play a role in developing China's vast western regions.
</P>
<P>
UNDP is now carrying out many projects in the area, she noted.
</P>
<P>
In the coming three years, UNDP will grant at least one billion
US dollars in loans to support the construction of infrastructure
facilities and water-conservation projects in the area, according
to the Leitner.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing is now using World Bank loans to start environmental
protection projects. The environment of Chongqing and the Three
Gorges Dam project area will be greatly improved once these
projects are finished.
</P>
<P>
Officials from UNESCO, the World Tourism Organization, and the
United Nations Industrial Development Organization also expressed
their willingness to support China's development of western area.
</P>
<P>
Incomplete statistics show that since 1978 China has got some
four billion US dollars in international aid, which was managed by
the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Eastern and coastal areas were the major beneficiaries of this
aid in the 1980s, according to officials from the ministry.
International organizations can play an important role in the
development of China's west, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
