<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on cooperation between
central China's Hubei Province and France opened in this
provincial capital city today.
</P>
<P>
French ambassador to China Pierre Morel, officials from French
city Bordeaux and representatives of over 30 noted French
companies attended the seminar, which was organized by the Hubei
provincial government and the general consulate of France to Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
Participants will concentrate on bilateral cooperation in the
fields of automobiles, education and urban construction.
</P>
<P>
