<HEADLINE> London's Millennium Bridge Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- London's first new crossing over
the Thames for more than 100 years opened to the public Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 320-meter-long Millennium footbridge, which links St Paul's
Cathedral with the new Tate Modern art gallery, costs 24 million U.
S. dollars and was designed by architect Norman Foster and British
sculptor Sir Anthony Car.
</P>
<P>
Around 4 million people are expected to use the bridge each
year, Reuters said.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is intended to look particularly striking when lit
up at night. Norman said it would form a "blade of light" across
the Thames.
</P>
<P>
More than half the money for the bridge came from Lottery funds.
Another bridge in London, Tower Bridge, opened in 1894. 
</P>
</TEXT>
