<HEADLINE> Photo Show Staged in HK to Boost Tourism in Shanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A photo show depicting the rich
cultural heritage in north China's Shanxi Province was staged here
today to promote the province's fledgling tourism.
</P>
<P>
About 100 photos covering every aspects of the life and legacy
of Shanxi on display were all produced by Wong Kam Chuen, director
and general manager of the Great Wall Travel Service, during his
visits to the province in the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Located in the eastern part of China's Loess Plateau, Shanxi is
believed to be one of the origins of Chinese civilization, with
evidence of human settlements over millions of years ago, thus
earning it the name of the "museum of ancient Chinese culture."
</P>
<P>
Known as China's largest coal producer, the province has now
turned to exploring its cultural and natural resources in a bid to
invigorate its economy, Han Heping, deputy director of the Shanxi
Provincial Tourism Bureau, told a press conference here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Han, who was in Hong Kong to attend a tourism product
exhibition in the week, said a direct flight from Hong Kong to
Taiyuan, the provincial capital of Shanxi, has now been put into
service to attract more foreign and Hong Kong visitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
