<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations has said a
shortage of 2.3 million tons of wheat has been recorded in the
drought-hit Afghanistan, the Associated Press of Pakistan reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that last year Afghanistan confronted a wheat
shortage of 1.1 million tons, but this year this shortage
increased to 2.3 million tons due to drought there.
</P>
<P>
Observers have said this is the worst drought in the country
during the last 30 years which may affect half of the Afghan
population. 
