<DOCNO> XIE20000610.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Resettlement Project for Development of China's West: Official ( 2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cai Fang, Director of the Institute of Population Science of
the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, said that in recent period
the population structure in the west will remain unchanged. The
population floating between the east and west will abide by law of
market economy.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the west which is economically and culturally
backward, labor force is surplus and high level talents are
deficient comparatively. Thus, China's west is now continuing to
transfer laborers to the east.
</P>
<P>
But, he said, the commercial opportunities promoted by the
development of China's west will absorb high-quality talents and
mature technical workers.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the success of the greater development of the west
China region, Chinese government and local governments in the east
have formulated a series policies to encourage talents to take
part in the development in the west.
</P>
<P>
According to the policies, the talented people can retain all
their relations in their original places in the east and they can
return to east at any time. The west region is also allow the
people to come and go freely.
</P>
<P>
Cai said the state stressed the importance to improve the
quality of the population in the west, for development of west
mainly depends on themselves.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the Ministry of Education has decided to
promote development of education in the west, especially in the
regions with ethnic population.
</P>
<P>
The universities and colleges in the eastern and central part
of China will expand enrollment to the students from the west and
they are encouraged to run well classes for students from Tibet
and Xinjiang and for other ethnic people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000610.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Resettlement Project for Development of China's West: Official ( 1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese official said here today
there is no large-sized resettlement project for the greater
development of west China region.
</P>
<P>
Li Shantong, Director of Regional Development Department of the
Development Research Center of the State Council, said that some
overseas media incorrectly reported that China will open up the
western region by huge resettlement project.
</P>
<P>
Some articles carried by overseas media claimed that China's
west will become a "container" for the increased population of the
country and in the coming years, the west is expected to hold
about 300 million people from the east.
</P>
<P>
"As far as I know, the central government does not have such a
project. At present, the principal task for the development of
China's west is to improve ecological environment and the
population quality," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Attending the Chongqing International Symposium on Development
of China's West, Li said unlike the development of the west part
of the United States, China's west is not a virgin land. There
are some population structure and central cities with stronger
radiation capacity in west China region.
</P>
<P>
He noted that comparing with the east, labor force in the west
are not deficient.
</P>
<P>
There are 10 provinces, autonomous regions and municipality in
China's west. The area and the population of the west accounts for
57 and 23 percent of the country's total respectively.
</P>
<P>
"Large-sized resettlement to the west will aggravate the
ecological environment and it is not a good way to follow," he
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
