<HEADLINE> Daily Report on Quality of Air in Key Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Taiyuan, Shenyang, Nanjing, Wuhan
and Guiyang had extremely slight air pollution today, according to
daily report issued by the China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Tianjin, Hohhot, Dalian, Changchun, Harbin, Hangzhou
Hefei, Fuzhou, Jinan, Qingdao, Yantai, Zhengzhou, Zhanjiang,
Chongqing, Chengdu, Xi'an and Urumqi enjoyed fairly good air.
</P>
<P>
Excellent air was reported in Wenzhou, Xiamen, Nanchang
Shenzhen, Shantou, Nanning, Haikou and Kunming.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Tianjin, Shenyang, Dalian, Harbin, Shanghai, Nanjing,
Suzhou Hangzhou, Xi'an, and 21 other cities listed absorbable
suspended particles as the major pollutants, while sulfur dioxide
was the major pollutant in Shijiazhuang, Guiyang and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The 42 cities include China's four municipalities directly
under the central government, the provincial and regional capitals
and 10 key coastal cities.  
</P>
