<HEADLINE> North Sri Lanka Sees Fierce Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Friday launched an attack on Tamil rebel positions in northern
Jaffna peninsula and fierce fighting flared up and continued for
several hours, according to an official release here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The release said the troops carried out the attack on general
area Sarasalai south to destroy a rebel stronghold. They
successfully demolished the rebel position and a few rebel bunkers
on the Sarasalai-Puttur road in the peninsula.
</P>
<P>
However, one officer and 24 soldiers were killed in action
while one officer and 49 others were injured during this operation,
the release said, adding that the Tamil rebels have suffered heavy
casualties.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan government troops last week stalled a massive Tamil
rebel offensive to recapture the Jaffna peninsula, the former
rebel stronghold which the rebels lost to the troops in 1996,
military sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, who have been fighting a war against the government
for a separate Tamil state in the country since 1983, carried out
a suicide bomb attack in the Colombo suburb of Ratmalana Wednesday,
killing a cabinet minister and 22 others and injuring more than 60
other people. 
</P>
