<HEADLINE> Another Tremor Jolts Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.9 on the
Richter scale jolted Bengkulu Province on the Sumatra island,
Indonesia,early Saturday morning (local time), an official said
here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was located in the Indian Ocean,
some 180 kilometers southwest of Bengkulu, capital of Bengkulu
Province,a spokesman for the Meteorology and Geophysics Agency,
Waan Tarmin,said.
</P>
<P>
Bengkulu was jolted by tens of aftershocks almost every day
following a deadly earthquake measuring 7.9 on the Richter scale
at 11:28 p.m.last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
At least 130 people died in the four-minute quake that threw
people off their beds. 
