<HEADLINE> Foreign-funded Ventures Honored for Boosting Tianjin Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin Municipality
has commended 119 foreign-funded ventures for their contributions
to local economy, praising them as a major driving force for the
local economic growth last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 39 such enterprises including Motorola China won the
title of "Best Foreign-funded Venture for 1999," with the Tianjin
Smith Kline &AMP; French Lab Ltd. winning the "Best Economic
Efficiency Prize" and another eight enterprises including the
Tianjin International Building Co. Ltd awarded for excellent
services.
</P>
<P>
At the awarding ceremony, Tianjin Mayor Li Shenglin said the
impending entry of China into the World Trade Organization will
allow Tianjin to open up further and he also pledged to create an
even more favorable investment environment for foreign-funded
enterprise in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Hailed as the biggest coastal city designated by the central
government for opening-up, Tianjin has so far approved more than
10,000 foreign-funded enterprises with 4,328 already going into
operation.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded ventures in Tianjin realized sales of more than
107 billion yuan in 1999 alone, with their output value, profit,
tax, and export accounting for 42 percent, 52.6 percent, 50
percent and 70.9 percent of the city's total, respectively.
</P>
