<HEADLINE> Strategy of Developing Western China Benefits Neighboring Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The implementation of the
strategy of developing China's western areas will facilitate
economic growth and social development in neighboring countries of
China, agreed experts attending an ongoing international symposium
on developing the west here.
</P>
<P>
Central Asian member nations of the Commonwealth of Independent
States (CIS) will benefit the most from the strategy since they
border on the western areas of China and the transportation is
very convenient between China and all these nations, said Li
Jingwen, an economist from the government think tank, the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Li, also an academician of the Russian Academy of Sciences,
said development in western China will boost in bilateral trade
with these CIS nations. Also, China and these CIS member nations
may join forces to better develop the natural resources in the
region such as petroleum and natural gas.
</P>
<P>
Echoing Li's view, a Russian official said better development
of China's west will create more demand, which the neighboring
countries could well make use of to boost their economy.
</P>
<P>
"Russia and CIS member nations in central Asia are very
interested in China's strategy of developing its west, and hope to
participate in the move." the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
