<HEADLINE> Anhui Steps up Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Eastern China's Anhui Province is
intensifying its effort for road construction with to form a basic
network of high-level highways in the province by the year 2020.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials in charge of highway management in Anhui
said the province has accelerated highways construction during the
past two years, building 404 kilometers of expressways during the
period.
</P>
<P>
Highway projects underway in the province now involve building
more than 500 kilometers of state-level or province-level highways,
at a cost of about 12 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province invested a total of 514 million yuan in highway
construction during the first four months this year, accounting
for 19.8 percent of the province's total fixed-asset investment
for 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
