<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newspaper Collector in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Li Hongxiang, a 74-year-old
retiree from Shijiazhuang City Post office in Hebei Province has
collected 13,000 kinds of newspapers in the last 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Li started his collection in 1981 when he found a newspaper
with his article. The earliest newspaper in his collection is the
first issue of "Shenbao," published during the Tongzhi period (
1862-1874) in the late Qing Dynasty (1644-1911). He has collected
56 newspapers issued before the founding of the People's Republic
in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The first issue of "People's Daily" published in 1948 in Li's
collection sold for 3,500 yuan (about 420 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Li has written some 25,000 letters to numerous newspaper
agencies across China for newspapers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
