</P>
<P>
Harbin Polytechnic University (HPU), known as a cradle for
Chinese engineers celebrated its 80th anniversary on June 7.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing sent a letter of congratulation to the
university saying that it has a long history of supplying talented
workers for the country, and many of them have become prominent in
the national defense and aerospace technology industries.
