</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Foreign shipping companies handle 30 percent of
Mexico's exports after the disappearance of the Mexican high-seas
merchant navy, and especially after the demise of the country's
container ships fleet, the private sector and exporting companies
announced.
</P>
<P>
Mexico misses an income of nearly 40 billion dollars in hard
currency with the control of the exports of commodities in
containers by foreign shipping companies, said the Confederation
of Industrial Chambers (Cocamin) Friday. (Mexico-Exports)
</P>
