<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's GDP Up by 6.3 Percent in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Gross National Product, defined as GDP adjusted for net
factor income from abroad, grew by 5.4 percent in the first
quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter, the value-added increase in manufacturing
and construction were 10.6 and 8 percent respectively. The
services sector contributed 53 percent to the overall GDP growth.
The contribution of manufacturing and construction sectors to the
growth were 25 percent and 10 percent respectively, the bank added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the bank said that Sri Lanka's growth of GDP is
expected to be five percent for the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
