<HEADLINE> Longo Wins Second Stage of Women's Challenge Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Jeannie Longo
of France won the second stage of the Women's Challenge cycling
race on Friday but Diana Ziliute of Lithuania took the overall
lead.
</P>
<P>
Longo, 41, who is preparing for her fifth Olympics, was
victorious in the 94 kilometers stage from Lowman to Stanley road
race. She completed the distance in two hours 25 minutes and three
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Ziliute, the reigning women's Tour de France champion, finished
second with the same time. Vera Hohlfeld of Germany was third in 2:
25:44.
</P>
<P>
Ziliute clocked five hours 11 minutes and four seconds in
overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Australian Anna wilson was second with 44 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
The 11-day, 1,007-kilometer race throughout Idaho continues
through June 18.
