<HEADLINE> French Skippers Keep Lead in Trans-Atlantic Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- French skippers held the leading
three places in the multi-hull division of the single-handed Trans-
Atlantic Race at the halfway point on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ellen MacArthur of Britain, the youngest skipper in the race,
led the mono-hulls.
</P>
<P>
Francis Joyon of France and his Eure et Loir 1 trimaran was one
mile ahead as he passed the halfway mark in the 2,800-mile race
from Plymouth to Newport, Rhode Island.
</P>
<P>
Chasing him hard was race favourite Alan Gautier, sailing
Foncia 1.
</P>
<P>
MacArthur, sailing Kingfisher 1, is the youngest skipper in the
40-year history of the race and leads 24 other Open 60-foot grand
prix boats.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Briton held an 11-mile lead on Friday over
Frenchman Roland Jourdain sailing Sill Beurre le Gall1.
</P>
<P>
The leading multi-hulls are expected to cross the finishing
line in Newport Rhode on Wednesday with the first mono-hulls
likely to finish two or three days later. 
</P>
