<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hamilton Wins Fifth Stage in Dauphine-Libere Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- American Tyler Hamilton won the fifth
stage of the Criterium du Dauphine-Libere cycling race on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hamilton completed the stage by clocking five hours 25 minutes
13 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Tour de France champion American Lance Armstrong finished
second with an identical time. He was the key to Hamilton's win on
the 201-kilometer haul from Baune de Venise to Digne-les-Bains.
</P>
<P>
Hamilton totalled 20 hours 22 minutes and 38 seconds in overall
stadnings, 44 seconds ahead of overnight leader Haimar Zubeldia of
Spain, with Armstrong another four seconds back. Fourth-placed
Swiss Alex Zuelle was almost two minutes behind.
</P>
<P>
A breakaway group opened a lead of five minutes 50 kilometers
from the finish and looked uncatchable, but several riders
including five members of Zubeldia's Euskalte team engaged in a
pursuit.
</P>
<P>
When Armstrong attacked, Hamilton was right behind and they
killed off the field, going 25 seconds clear with 15 kilometers to
climb to the finish at Digne and 46 seconds when they arrived.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
