<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Weekly (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are the highlights
of diplomatic news released by Xinhua in the past week.
</P>
<P>
Myanmese Leader Visits China
</P>
<P>
Maung Aye, Vice-Chairman of the State Peace and Development
Council of Myanmar, began his China visit on Monday at the
invitation of Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Beijing, Maung Aye conferred with Chinese
leaders and made discussions on bilateral ties and other issues of
common concern.
</P>
<P>
The two countries signed a joint statement on the framework of
the future bilateral relations and cooperations.
</P>
<P>
Maung Aye also attended activities marking the 50th anniversary
of the establishment of the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Moldova President Tours China
</P>
<P>
Moldova President Petru Lucinschi arrived at Beijing Wednesday
morning on a state visit to China from June 7-12 at the invitation
of Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
The two countries issued a joint statement.
</P>
<P>
Lucinschi and his entourage also toured Kunming, the capital
city of southwest China's Yunnan province, and Shenzhen, a port
city in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
