<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Weekly (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang and Putin Talk over Phone
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin on Thursday described this year
as "an unusual year" for Sino-Russian relations in his
conversation with Russian President Vladimir Putin over the
hotline phone.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state next month will meet in Dushanbe,
capital of Tajikistan, and Beijing, respectively, during which
they will have an extensive and in-depth exchange of views on all
issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said China and Russia, as big countries
and permanent members of the United Nations Security Council, are
highly responsible in safeguarding international peace and
security.
</P>
<P>
The mutual trust and close cooperation between the two
countries are in the fundamental interest of the two countries and
conducive to world peace and stability, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
NPC Chairman to Visit Six European and Asian Countries
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry announced on Tuesday that Li Peng,
Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC) of China, will pay an official goodwill visit to
the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, the Republic of Slovenia, the
Republic of Croatia, the Republic of Slovakia, the Republic of
Azerbaijan and Ukraine from June 11-26.
</P>
<P>
Li is invited by the parliaments and governments of the above
six countries.
</P>
<P>
Li will have an extensive contact with the leaders, members of
parliaments, and people from all walks of life of the six
countries, so as to push for the sound and stable development of
the relations between China and these countries in the spirit of
promoting understanding, enhancing trust, strengthening friendship
and deepening cooperation. 
</P>
