accountable for their actions."  (UN-Personnel-Annan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Russia on Friday offered NATO a joint missile
defense proposal but the NATO chief said the plan was still short
on details.
</P>
<P>
Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev explained to the western
military alliance about the joint European anti-missile defense
system Russian President Vladimir Putin had put forward days ago.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Sergeyev avoided questions
concerning details of the Russian proposal and only went so far as
to say that the Russian proposal would not breach the 1972 Anti-
Ballistic Missile treaty.  (Russia-NATO-Joint Plan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentine President Fernando de la Rua said
Friday that the general strike called by the three labor central
is "unnecessary and useless."
</P>
<P>
The president admitted before the local press that the country
faces a very difficult economic situation, especially because of
the big trade deficit.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the government took "painful" measures to
solve the serious problems of the balance of trade deficit, and
said that this policy aims at the development and growth of the
country with social equality, giving attention to social problems.
(Argentina-Strike)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Vladimir Putin will pay an official
visit to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) this
Summer to "promote Russia's role in normalizing the situation on
the Korean peninsula," the Russian Foreign Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Chairman of the DPRK Defense Commission
Kim Jong Il, President Putin "will shortly visit Pyongyang" and
this will be "our head of state's first official visit to the
country in the whole history of Russia," the ministry said in a
statement. (Russia-Putin-Korea-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PYONGYANG -- The United States regards the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) as an imaginary enemy with ulterior
motives so as to achieve military Hegemonism, a commentary of the
Korean Central News Agency said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Strobe Talbott, deputy secretary of the U.S. State Department,
officially made a provocative statement at a press conference on
June 4 that the DPRK is the imaginary enemy of the U.S. "national
missile defense" initiative, according to the commentary.  (DPRK-
U.S.-Talbott)  
</P>
