<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Johnson Wins 200m in Seville Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Madrid, June 9 (Xinhua) -- American star Michael Johnson
produced the second fastest 200 meters in the world this year when
he ran 19.91 seconds at the Seville Athletics Grand Prix II
meeting on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The time has only been beaten by the world record holder
himself -- the American ran an altitude-assisted 19.71 in South
Africa in March.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's Noah Ngeny, men's 1,500m world championship silver
medallist last year, won the 3,000m gold in a time of seven
minutes 35.46 seconds, the fastest time in the world this year,
followed by morocco's Brahim Lahlafi and Mohamed El Wardi.
</P>
<P>
The men's 1,500m champion went to Hicham El Guerrouj of Morocco,
who clocked three minutes 33.48 seconds.
</P>
<P>
American Nanceen Perry won the women's 200m in 22.97. Hasna
Benhassi of Morocco took the women's 800m title by clocking two
minutes 0.11 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The women's 5,000m title was wrested by Nirhane Adere of
Ethiopia who registered 15 minutes 8.39 seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
