<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Calls for No Incidents in Euro 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Foreign Ministry
expressed desire on Friday to avoid incidents that might
overshadow Turkish team's successes in the forthcoming Euro-2000
Football Championship.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said in a statement that measures,
including several warnings, had been taken in view of the Euro-
2000 that will take place in the Netherlands and Belgium between
June 10 and July 2.
</P>
<P>
It added that a seven-member group had also been formed to
serve Turkish spectators.
</P>
<P>
Recalling that some unpleasant events had occurred in Istanbul
and Copenhagen prior to UEFA Cup games, the statement said the
Foreign Ministry had thought it beneficial to warn the Turkish
citizens living in the Netherlands and Belgium against possible
provocations in order to prevent re-occurrence of similar
incidents during Euro-2000.
</P>
<P>
"We wish that all Turkish citizens should stay away from
attitudes and violence that may overshadow the Turkish team's
successes and harm the prestige of Turkey," it said. "Turkish
people and supporters, who watch the games, should behave calmly
without paying attention to provocations."
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry established a seven-person mission force
to help and guide the Turkish team players and supporters during
the Euro-2000.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the mission force had been giving services
in the Netherlands since June 4, and it would extend every
assistance and facility to the Turkish supporters in Arnhem,
Eindhoven and Brussels soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
