al-Assad who courageously joined hands with Egypt in its glorious
October War (against Israel) in 1973," it added.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak called Assad's death "an enormous loss for his people
and the nation." He wished Syria "complete national unity" after
the death of Assad, whom he hailed as "the most noble partner in
the battle of peace."
</P>
<P>
Egypt has declared three days of mourning for Assad, 69, who
died of heart attack. 
