<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Deplores Death of Syrian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia on Saturday
expressed deep sorrow at the death of Syrian President Hafez al-
Assad, who died of heart attack earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi Press Agency monitored here quoted a statement from
the Saudi Royal Diwan as saying that the "kingdom is in mourning
due to the passing away of the Syrian president who dedicated his
life to both the Arab and the Muslim world."
</P>
<P>
The statement said Syria had achieved development and
modernization during Assad's leadership in the past three decades.
</P>
<P>
