<HEADLINE> Colombian Government, Rebels Ask International Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of the government
and of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) concurred
Saturday in the need of having the international community
cooperate in the peace process of this country.
</P>
<P>
Government delegate Favio Valencia Cossio and FARC leader Raul
Reyes are the main actors in the International Conference on "The
peace process in Colombia," going on in the Alcala de Henares
municipality.
</P>
<P>
Reyes said that "international assistance must not have a
military character, because that would be intervention, more war.
The real assistance is more resources to solve the problems of the
people."
</P>
<P>
The meeting sponsored by the Organization of Solidarity with
the Peoples of Asia, Africa, and Latin America (OSPAAAL), an
independent entity, began this Saturday and will end Sunday in
Alcala de Henares, 30 kilometers east of Madrid.
</P>
<P>
Valencia agreed with the guerrilla leader that "international
cooperation must come simultaneously with the process of peace,
even as observers of the agreements we may arrive at, but without
intervening."
</P>
<P>
Both leaders said that the solution for Colombia is the table
of talks set by the government and the guerrilla.
</P>
<P>
The government representative said that the solution does not
only goes through the resolution of the armed conflict, but also
through "overcoming the violence caused by various sectors,
because we must remember that 32,000 homicides are committed in
Colombia every year."
</P>
<P>
Valencia described drug trafficking as "the main enemy of peace
in Colombia."
</P>
<P>
He said that "drug trafficking is an international crime and we
ask collaboration not as a gift, but as an alliance to combat the
worst scourge of humanity."
</P>
<P>
This is the first conference in which government and guerrilla
publicly expose their plans, backed by many representatives of the
Colombian civil society and European organizations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
