<HEADLINE> Colombian Rebel Members Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Fifth Army Brigade, with headquarters in Bucaramanga,
Santander department capital, said that the three National
Liberation Army (ELN) rebels died in confrontations with
government troops who fought the rebels when these were erecting
an illegal checkpoint on a road of the region.
</P>
<P>
Four members of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (
FARC) were shot dead by army troops in the Cauca mountains.
</P>
<P>
Other two members of the FARC Front No. 4 died when a mined
field they had installed in the rural zone of the Yondo
municipality of the Antioquia department detonated, informed the
Third Brigade in Medellin, the department capital.
</P>
<P>
The FARC has been holding peace talks with the government since
October of last year, while government delegates and ELN
representatives are negotiating to open a similar process.
</P>
</TEXT>
