<HEADLINE> Seismic Swarms Observed in Nicaraguan Volcano Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Most of the seisms were located in a small zone on the southern
slope of the 1,282 meters above sea level volcano, said INETER.
</P>
<P>
The seisms were felt in the Nicaraguan Electricity Company (
ENEL) geothermal plant, that operates in the place, said the
communique.
</P>
<P>
The INETER said that Friday at 13:00 a continuous seismic
tremor was observed in the volcano, which indicates that the
seismic activity is not only caused by movements of the tectonic
faults, but that it is a volcanic process.
</P>
<P>
Similar swarms were observed in August of 1999, the stronger of
them with a 4.1 degree intensity on the Richter scale, which made
authorities evacuate some 500 residents of nearby communities.
</P>
