<HEADLINE> Italian PM Sends Condolences on Death of Assad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Italian Premier Giuliano Amato on
Saturday sent Italy's condolences to the Syrian government on the
death of President Hafez el Assad.
</P>
<P>
In his message, Amato expressed the hope that his death would
not hinder the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the premier's office said Italy will be
represented at Assad state funeral on Monday by Senate Speaker
Nicola Mancino.
</P>
<P>
Assad, 69, had led Syria since 1971 and was said to have died
in Damascus this morning. He was last seen in public on May 8 when
he traveled to Cairo to meet with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Assad, who would have turned 70 in October, had been in poor
health for years and his condition deteriorated significantly over
the past few weeks.
</P>
<P>
Assad was first elected president in March 1971 and was re-
elected five times, the last in March 1999 for another seven-year
term.
</P>
</TEXT>
